name: Adnan Syed
summary: The Maryland Supreme Court has ordered a new hearing in the case of Adnan Syed, who was convicted in 2000 of murdering his ex-girlfriend Hae Min Lee. The court upheld Syed's conviction but ruled that a lower court erred in granting him a new trial in 2016. The new hearing will focus on whether Syed's attorney provided ineffective assistance during his trial. Syed's case gained national attention in 2014 when it was featured in the first season of the popular podcast "Serial." The podcast raised questions about the evidence used to convict Syed and sparked a renewed interest in the case.

name: Artem domestic violence
summary: Artem Chigvintsev, a professional dancer on "Dancing with the Stars," was arrested on suspicion of domestic violence. According to a 911 call, Chigvintsev's wife, Nikki Garcia, claimed that he threw shoes at her. Chigvintsev was arrested and charged with domestic violence and is currently not scheduled to return as a pro for Season 33 of "Dancing with the Stars." The news was widely reported by outlets such as TMZ, Variety, NBC News, The Associated Press, USA Today, ABC News, Us Weekly, the Los Angeles Times, CBS San Francisco, and Page Six. Nikki Garcia has requested privacy for her family following the arrest.

name: Wheelchair basketball Paralympics
summary: In the 2024 Paralympics, wheelchair basketball teams from various countries participated and made significant headlines. Team USA's men's wheelchair basketball squad began their campaign with a victory over Spain, marking a successful start to their tournament. Paris 2024 Paralympics featured wheelchair basketball, goalball, sitting volleyball, and wheelchair rugby as team sports, with Google honoring these events with a commemorative Paralympic-themed Doodle. The United States' wheelchair basketball team, boasting a strong legacy, holds training grounds at UW-Whitewater University. Paralympic veteran Nate Hinze competed with his son, making the occasion a family affair. France's wheelchair basketball team aimed to make a triumphant comeback after their absence from the previous Paralympics. The International Wheelchair Basketball Federation (IWBF) provided insights into the men's competition, highlighting the athletes and teams to watch. Iowans AJ Fitzpatrick and Jeromie Meyer represented Team USA in wheelchair basketball at the Paralympics, showcasing the depth of talent in the sport.
